originalText.text: I took the 2 day trip to Washington DC with this company. The receptionists were very professional and very accommodating to us when we had to change our pick up location. Our tour was bilingual and we were lucky to have two tour guides Mia and Candice. They took care of us and did an excellent job in showing us the places and translating for my Chinese parents. The visits were well organized planned so it all went smoothly without much wait in an otherwise hectic tourist destination such as the Capitol. I was able to charge my phone in the bus and it had a good working AC which was a relief in such a humid couple of days. I would definitely use this company again to experience other tours but most importantly I feel comfortable sending away my non English speaking parents with them.

originalText.text: This was the first time my boyfriend and I went on a trip with Tinma aka Eworld. It was a lot of fun! We were able to do so much within the 2 day trip. Our travel guide, Sherry was helpful, with, and organized. She planned our two day trip itinerary very well and she was quick on her toes. There were moments when we were either stuck in traffic or someone on the tour was late in coming back to the bus and it would delay our events schedule. However, even with the delays, Sherry was able to figure something out and to ensure we were able to have time to see Niagara falls, get on the Maid of the Mist, and the fireworks at night. We visited the Thousand Islands and was able to eat at a delicious buffet on our last day. She was able to give us so much information about areas around the locations and the locations themselves. Overall the trip was memorable and entertaining! Thanks, Sherry!
